accessorName.description: Output field. Internal name of the accessor record.

apiVersion.description: Matching field. API version (combination of minor and major versions). Allows overriding authorization rules level of specific API version. Supported wildcard value "null". Same value should be in Authorization Validation web app endpoint configuration.

appName.description: Matching field. Client software name, hardcoded on the client side. E.g. name of the app. Supported wildcard value "Any".

appVersion.description: Matching field. Client software platform name (iOS, Android, React), hardcoded on the client side. E.g. name of the app. Supported wildcard value "Any".

endpoint.description: Matching field. Endpoint ID/object as configured on web app instance (granting server). Allows overriding authorization rules level of specific endpoint. Supported wildcard value "null". Same value should be in Authorization Validation web app endpoint configuration.

isForbidden.description: Optional output field. Indicates that this specific accessor is banned - for Accessor authentication provider. E.g. to restrict clients with outdated unsupported API versions

lookupPriority.description: Internal field. Priority for Accessor identity provider matching. All accessor definitions are sorted with this field - and those with higher priority - matched first within Accessor authentication provider

parentAccessor.description: Optional output field. Indicates the accessor record containing configuration groups (Authorizations, Identities, Scopes) - which are not defined at this child accessor level

platform.description: Matching field. Client software platform name (iOS, Android, React), hardcoded on the client side. E.g. name of the app. Supported wildcard value "Any".

product.description: Matching field. Application product. Allows overriding authorization rules level of specific product. Supported wildcard value "Any".

productGroup.description: Matching field. Application product group. Allows overriding authorization rules level of specific product group. Supported wildcard value "Any".

user.description: Matching field. Application user. Allows overriding authorization rules level of specific user. Supported wildcard value "Any".

Accessor.description: Consumed by Accessor Authentication Provider (e.g. Accessor_data module). Groups authorization rules (Authorization, Identity, Scope definitions). Defines Set of client software allowed (or restricted) for accessing the API - and their corresponding identification mappings.

authenticationName.description: Defines the Granting Server -> Authentication Provider name

functionalFieldSet.description: Functional key fields returned by Authentication module/Authentication provider to accessor

keyFieldSet.description: Data Authorization key fields returned by Authentication module/Authentication provider to accessor

privateDataFieldSet.description: Private portion of Authentication data, required to be provided by accessors

publicDataFieldSet.description: Public portion of Authentication data, required to be provided by accessors

Authentication.description: Defines a set of input (public, private) and output (keys, functional) data as well as the Granting Server -> Authentication Provider name
